You are getting an error because of **WHERE you declared the delegate** ğŸ‘‡

This line is illegal in C#:

```csharp
public delegate void Mydel(int a , int b);
```

You placed it **inside the Main method**, but in C#:

> âŒ Delegates CANNOT be declared inside methods
> âœ… Delegates must be declared at class or namespace level

---

## âŒ Your incorrect code structure

```csharp
static void Main(string[] args)
{
    public delegate void Mydel(int a , int b);  // âŒ Not allowed here
}
```

---

# âœ… Correct Way to Declare Delegate

Move the delegate OUTSIDE the method but INSIDE the namespace or class.

### âœ”ï¸ Fixed and Working Code

```csharp
namespace Delegates
{
    // âœ… Delegate declared at namespace level
    public delegate void Mydel(int a, int b);

    internal class Program
    {
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Mydel del = add;   // Assign method to delegate
            del(10, 20);       // Invoke delegate
        }

        public static void add(int a, int b)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(a + b);
        }
    }
}
```

### âœ… Output

```
30
```

---

# ğŸ”¥ Important Rules About Delegates

| Rule             | Valid         |
| ---------------- | ------------- |
| Inside Method    | âŒ Not allowed |
| Inside Class     | âœ… Allowed     |
| Inside Namespace | âœ… Allowed     |

---

# âœ… Correct Structure Pattern

```csharp
delegate returntype DelegateName(parameters);

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        // use delegate here
    }
}
```

---

# âœ… What you learned

âœ” Delegate must be declared outside methods
âœ” Method signature must match delegate
âœ” Method should be static if used in static Main

---

# âœ… Alternate Fix (Inside Class)

```csharp
namespace Delegates
{
    internal class Program
    {
        public delegate void Mydel(int a, int b);

        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            Program p = new Program();
            Mydel d = p.add;
            d(5, 10);
        }

        public void add(int a, int b)
        {
            Console.WriteLine(a + b);
        }
    }
}
```

---

# ğŸ§  Interview Tip

> Delegate must be declared at class or namespace level, not inside a method.

